		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://ventureburn.com/?p=200480</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Techcyte has recently closed a funding round of $15 million, led by Van Tuyl Companies. This is an exciting milestone for the company and its aspirations to steadily stay on</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/techcyte-raises-15m-to-expand-ai-diagnostics-platform/" data-wpel-link="internal">Techcyte Raises $15M to Expand AI Diagnostics Platform</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://techcyte.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Techcyte </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">has recently closed a funding round of $15 million, led by Van Tuyl Companies. This is an exciting milestone for the company and its aspirations to steadily stay on a trajectory to profitability and to expand its platform &#8216;Fusion&#8217; into new sectors, including medical, veterinary and environmental health.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Many large existing strategic partners, as well as new strategic partners, such as Zoetis, the world leader in animal health, and the Mayo Clinic, the broadest group of medical specialists, were also present for the </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/earlybird-vc-raises-e360m-for-new-european-tech-funds/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">round</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">. Due to the rapidly increasing dependence on AI and the chronic shortage of personnel in diagnostic laboratories worldwide, as well as rising test volume.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Bridging the Gap in Clinical and Anatomic Pathology</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company has been developing digital pathology solutions since 2013, giving them over 10 years of experience. Their lightest offering, the Techcyte Fusion®, is developed to be the first digital workflow that integrates anatomic and clinical pathology.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;As laboratories are asked to do more with fewer resources and higher demands for quality and turnaround time&#8221;, said Ben Cahoon, CEO of Techcyte, &#8220;TechcyteFusion directly responds to these challenges with integrated workflows driven by artificial intelligence. This investment allows us to continue growing the platform and extending the world-class capabilities we’ve built in collaboration with Mayo Clinic.&#8221;</span></p>
<div id="attachment_200481" style="width: 490px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-200481" class="size-full wp-image-200481" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/logo-Techcyte.jpg" alt="Techcyte logo" width="480" height="108" /><p id="caption-attachment-200481" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Techcyte</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The platform uses deep learning algorithms that help pathologists identify parasitic cells, bacteria and cancer cells more consistently than a manual microscope observation. It also digitises the samples for telepathology, enabling remote case review from any part of the world.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/earlybird-vc-raises-e360m-for-new-european-tech-funds/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Earlybird VC Raises €360M for New European Tech Funds</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">A Data-Driven Competitive Edge</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">A standout feature of this funding deal is the expanded access to Mayo Clinic’s Safe Harbour dataset. This massive repository includes over 17 million de-identified slides and pathology reports, providing Techcyte with one of the most robust training grounds for medical AI in existence.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This access is expected to dramatically accelerate the development of new diagnostic tests and improve the accuracy of existing algorithms. The company’s veterinary segment is already profitable, a feat rare in the high-burn world of med-tech, and Techcyte expects its human and environmental segments to reach the same milestone by 2027.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Expanding the Partner Ecosystem</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Techcyte&#8217;s business model is based on openness and interoperability. Instead of tying up labs with a proprietary piece of hardware, the Fusion platform is engineered to connect with numerous digital slide scanners, lab information systems, and external AI developers.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Recent attempts at collaborations, such as the 2025 research collaboration with Modella AI to include PathChat (a copilot generative AI for pathologists), show Techcyte&#8217;s intent to stay close to the cutting edge of the agentic AI trend in medicine.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">As the global healthcare system shifts toward a digital-first model, Techcyte’s latest capital injection positions it to be the foundational software layer for the next generation of diagnostic labs.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/techcyte-raises-15m-to-expand-ai-diagnostics-platform/" data-wpel-link="internal">Techcyte Raises $15M to Expand AI Diagnostics Platform</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
