		<title>Netomi Raises $110M to Power AI Customer Experiences</title>
		<link>https://ventureburn.com/netomi-raises-110m-to-power-ai-customer-experiences/</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Ekemini]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Fri, 01 May 2026 11:19:01 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Venture Capital]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://ventureburn.com/?p=200474</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Netomi, the leading provider of enterprise AI in customer service, announced that it has secured $110 million in Series C funding. The funding was led by Accenture Ventures, with participation</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/netomi-raises-110m-to-power-ai-customer-experiences/" data-wpel-link="internal">Netomi Raises $110M to Power AI Customer Experiences</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1qCJkIfXB0_TII6OwrP7xIGT0YdjoEj5qfYKs-tASjXM/edit?tab=t.0#heading=h.16hl6qyt5up5" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Netomi</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">, the leading provider of enterprise AI in customer service, announced that it has secured $110 million in Series C </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/earlybird-vc-raises-e360m-for-new-european-tech-funds/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">funding</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">. </span>The funding was led by Accenture Ventures, with participation from Adobe Ventures, WndrCo, SLW, NAVER Ventures, Metis Strategy, and Fin Capital.</p>
<p>The new funding brings Netomi&#8217;s total funding to around $160 million and affirms its position in the fast-growing AI CX market. Credibility is further added by the round with participation of AI pioneers such as Greg Brockman, Demis Hassabis, and Mustafa Suleyman. This is a significant vote of confidence by the industry for the &#8220;agentic&#8221; approach to automation pioneered by Netomi.</p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Moving Beyond Chatbots to &#8220;Agentic&#8221; AI</span></h2>
<p>While customers have endured a decade of frustrating chatbots, Netomi is ushering in the Age of Agentic CX. Whereas other bots sit at the edges of the website, Netomi’s platform is driven by AI agents embedded in the core. The agents don’t know the answer; they predict needs and make decisions, doing a refund and restocking shipping orders.</p>
<div id="attachment_200475" style="width: 410px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-200475" class="wp-image-200475 size-full" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/netomi.jpg" alt="netomi" width="400" height="400" /><p id="caption-attachment-200475" class="wp-caption-text">Source: netomi</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">“Agentic AI begins a whole new chapter for the customer experience,” says Ndidi Oteh, CEO of Accenture Song. “One that lets brands respond with a deeper understanding, consistency, and intelligence at all touchpoints. Netomi’s platform doesn’t just bring faster service; it opens a new era of emotional connection between people and brands they love.”</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News:</span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/earlybird-vc-raises-e360m-for-new-european-tech-funds/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400"> Earlybird VC Raises €360M for New European Tech Funds</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Battle-Tested in High-Stakes Environments</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Netomi has proved itself able to thrive in &#8220;highest stakes&#8221; settings where failures and outages aren&#8217;t tolerated. Its client base includes global behemoths like United Airlines, Delta Air Lines, Paramount and DraftKings.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The platform&#8217;s tech savviness has been leveraged in high-profile sporting events. </span>At DraftKings’ platform, Netomi’s AI managed spikes of over 40,000 customer requests per second. At Paramount, it was live in under 2 weeks for their Paramount+ platform. Netomi is built for these kinds of environments, where failure is not an option, said Puneet Mehta. With Accenture, we provide corporations with a direct “on-ramp” to how the future of AI is built.</p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Strategic Partnerships with Accenture and Adobe</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This funding comes with a huge strategic change in distribution. Accenture has partnered with Netomi in a global alliance to build a &#8220;deployment playbook&#8221; for an enterprise agentic CX. This gives Accenture the ability to incorporate Netomi’s AI into existing client systems with zero disruptions.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Moreover, the financing from Adobe Ventures signals a trend toward &#8220;experience orchestration&#8221;. Since 99% of the Fortune 100 use Adobe products, integrating Netomi&#8217;s AI adds value to an invisible, proactive brand layer.<br />
</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/netomi-raises-110m-to-power-ai-customer-experiences/" data-wpel-link="internal">Netomi Raises $110M to Power AI Customer Experiences</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
			</item>
