		<title>Earlybird VC Raises €360M for New European Tech Funds</title>
		<link>https://ventureburn.com/earlybird-vc-raises-e360m-for-new-european-tech-funds/</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Ekemini]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Thu, 30 Apr 2026 11:22:59 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Venture Capital]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://ventureburn.com/?p=200469</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Earlybird Venture Capital has successfully completed its 8th early-stage fund (Fund VIII) at €360m. The new raise is the largest in its 29-year history and highlights a shift in focus</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/earlybird-vc-raises-e360m-for-new-european-tech-funds/" data-wpel-link="internal">Earlybird VC Raises €360M for New European Tech Funds</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://earlybird.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Earlybird Venture Capital</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> has successfully completed its 8th early-stage </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/squads-raises-18m-to-expand-stablecoin-platform/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">fund </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">(Fund VIII) at €360m. The new raise is the largest in its 29-year history and highlights a shift in focus to the architecture of AI and deep technology.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This oversubscribed fund comes at a time of real need for European venture capital. Earlybird has weathered the world economic storms that have taken place and has kept up its normal four-year cycle. Each three to four years the firm has raised a new one; since it launched in 1997, each fund has increased the size of the firm&#8217;s AUM to €2.5 billion.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">A Strategic Bet on the AI Stack</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">While many investors have rushed toward AI applications, Earlybird Fund VIII is doubling down on the plumbing of the digital age. The investment team, led by partners Dr Hendrik Brandis, Dr Christian Nagel, and Dr Andre Retterath, is prioritising infrastructure, hardware, and foundational models where defensibility and profit margins are typically higher.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_200470" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-200470" class="size-large wp-image-200470" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/venture-capital-1024x683.jpg" alt="venture capital" width="1024" height="683" /><p id="caption-attachment-200470" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Unsplash</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;At the application layer, it has never been easier to build a product, but that also makes it noisier and more competitive,&#8221; explained general partner Dr Andre Retterath. &#8220;We are looking deeper into the stack where the moats are wider and the barriers to entry are significantly higher.&#8221;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Earlybird has already deployed capital from the new fund into several high-profile ventures, including the following:</span></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Black Forest Labs:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> The German image-generation powerhouse behind the Flux models.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Spatial AI:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> A pioneer in 3D AI foundation models.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Arago:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> A specialist in photonic computing.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/squads-raises-18m-to-expand-stablecoin-platform/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Squads Raises $18M to Expand Stablecoin Platform</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">The Perpetual Ownership Revolution</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Beyond the capital raise, Earlybird is making waves with a radical restructuring of its partnership. With Fund VIII, the firm has introduced a &#8220;perpetual active ownership model&#8221;.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Under this new framework, Earlybird will remain entirely owned by its active partners. Unlike many peer firms that have explored partial sales to private equity or external management companies, Earlybird’s model ensures that when a partner leaves, their ownership is transferred back to the active GPs. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This is a deliberate effort to remain independent and ensure that the people running the firm are the ones with skin in the game for the next generation.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Sharpening the European Focus</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The close of Fund VIII also marks the first major milestone since Earlybird simplified its corporate structure. Since splitting out its Central and Eastern European operations, focused Digital East division (now rebranded) to become an independent company in late 2024, the main Earlybird team has focused firmly on western European centres, including Frankfurt, Stockholm and Amsterdam, while deploying the dedicated Earlybird Health stream.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Earlybird&#8217;s newest €360m war chest joins a portfolio that is already stacked with legends such as N26, UiPath and Isar Aerospace. But it also sets the firm up to take the next &#8216;sovereign&#8217; European wave of tech companies building not just apps but also the grids and physical infrastructure of tomorrow.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/earlybird-vc-raises-e360m-for-new-european-tech-funds/" data-wpel-link="internal">Earlybird VC Raises €360M for New European Tech Funds</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
			</item>
