					<description><![CDATA[<p>Legora reported a final close to its Series D at $600M, an uplift to its valuation to $5.6 billion on a post-money basis. The announcement indicates that this is a</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/legora-raises-600m-hits-5-6b-valuation-in-ai-boom/" data-wpel-link="internal">Legora Raises $600M, Hits $5.6B Valuation in AI Boom</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://legora.com/" data-wpel-link="external" rel="external noopener noreferrer"><span style="font-weight: 400">Legora </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">reported a final close to its </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/squads-raises-18m-to-expand-stablecoin-platform/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Series </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">D at $600M, an uplift to its valuation to $5.6 billion on a post-money basis. The announcement indicates that this is a $50M extension to the round that was first announced in March.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The strategic top-off also manages to bring heavyweight corporate backers NVIDIA (via NVentures) and Atlassian, the first significant high-profile move to the legal-tech vertical for NVIDIA. They join an impressive line-up of investors like Accel, Benchmark and Bessemer Venture Partners.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">From Chatbots to Legal Agents</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The massive capital injection highlights a pivot in the AI market: the move from passive chat interfaces to autonomous agents. While early legal AI tools focused on simple summarisation, Legora is building what CEO and co-founder Max Junestrand calls an agentic operating system for law.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_200464" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-200464" class="size-large wp-image-200464" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Lady-Justice-1024x683.jpg" alt="Lady Justice" width="1024" height="683" /><p id="caption-attachment-200464" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Unsplash</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;Foundation models are improving rapidly, but the real breakthrough is in how they&#8217;re applied,&#8221; Junestrand said in a statement. &#8220;We are moving beyond AI that simply assists to AI that executes complex, multi-step legal workflows with human oversight.&#8221;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The technology is built directly into the firm&#8217;s wide data and knowledge of the jurisdiction, so it has the ability to perform end-to-end tasks such as multi-jurisdictional research and complex contract drafting and review.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/squads-raises-18m-to-expand-stablecoin-platform/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Squads Raises $18M to Expand Stablecoin Platform</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Record-Breaking Growth Metrics</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Legora&#8217;s type of financial growth is unheard of in the enterprise software space. Legora has just crossed the $100M in annual recurring revenue (ARR) mark, only 18 months after its general launch.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The scale of its operations has expanded in the following manner:</span></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Workforce: </b><span style="font-weight: 400">Increased from 40 to over 400 workers over the last 12 months.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Global Presence:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> Now services 1,000+ companies in 50+ markets Including global legal majors White &amp; Case, Linklaters, and Cleary Gottlieb.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Client Impact:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> Law firms using the platform report saving an average of 4.3 non-billable hours per lawyer each week.</span></li>
</ul>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">The Competition for the Legal Stack</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The $600m war chest gives Legora the ability to directly compete with its nearest competitor, Harvey, which is currently valued at around $8b and has OpenAI and a16z supporting it. While Harvey has led the conversation in the U.S., LeGora has doubled down on being European and created a suite that can deal with complex multilingual jurisdictional needs.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">As part of the new funding, where they will be seeking to ramp up their U.S. expansion, Legora intends to focus on legal departments within Fortune 500 companies such as Barclays, as in-house teams are increasingly turning to automation to handle large volumes of compliance and litigation-related tasks.</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/legora-raises-600m-hits-5-6b-valuation-in-ai-boom/" data-wpel-link="internal">Legora Raises $600M, Hits $5.6B Valuation in AI Boom</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
