		<title>Rocsys Raises $13M, Launches Robotaxi Charging System</title>
		<link>https://ventureburn.com/rocsys-raises-13m-launches-robotaxi-charging-system/</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Ekemini]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Thu, 30 Apr 2026 11:06:13 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Venture Capital]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://ventureburn.com/?p=200459</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>While the world has focused on the complex software required to make cars drive themselves, a quieter logistical bottleneck has threatened the scalability of the robotaxi industry: who plugs them</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/rocsys-raises-13m-launches-robotaxi-charging-system/" data-wpel-link="internal">Rocsys Raises $13M, Launches Robotaxi Charging System</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><span style="font-weight: 400">While the world has focused on the complex software required to make cars drive themselves, a quieter logistical bottleneck has threatened the scalability of the robotaxi industry: who plugs them in? Today, Dutch-American startup </span><a href="https://www.rocsys.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Rocsys </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">announced a major step toward solving this &#8220;last inch&#8221; of automation, securing a $13 million </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/hightouch-raises-150m-to-expand-data-activation-tools/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Series </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">A extension and launching the Rocsys M1, the world’s first hands-free charging system designed for multi-bay robotaxi operations.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The Series B financing round is led by Capricorn Partners and Scania Invest and jointly supported by Forward.One, SEB Greentech Venture Capital and Graduate Ventures. This raises investment in the company up to $56 million. The investment will be used to quickly deploy the M1 system in North America and Europe as fleets gear up for a major transition into autonomous mobility by 2027.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Solving the Depot Bottleneck</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The current irony of the autonomous vehicle (AV) industry is that even the most advanced self-driving cars still require human intervention at the depot. Manual charging introduces safety risks, high labour costs, and operational downtime.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The Rocsys M1 changes this dynamic by utilizing an overhead rail-mounted robotic arm. Unlike previous iterations that served a single vehicle, one M1 unit can slide along its rail to serve up to 10 different parking bays. Using AI-driven computer vision and patented &#8220;soft robotics&#8221; technology, the M1 identifies the vehicle’s charging port and connects the plug with more than 99.9% accuracy, regardless of lighting or weather conditions.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_200460" style="width: 812px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-200460" class="size-full wp-image-200460" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Rocsys_Logo.jpg" alt="Rocsys Logo" width="802" height="252" /><p id="caption-attachment-200460" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Rocsys</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">“Autonomous vehicles are growing rapidly, and infrastructure must keep pace,” said Crijn Bouman, CEO and Co-founder of Rocsys. “Without hands-free operations, autonomy stops at the depot. The M1 is the missing link for robotaxi operators to move from pilots to global deployment.”</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/hightouch-raises-150m-to-expand-data-activation-tools/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Hightouch Raises $150M to Expand Data Activation Tools</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">High Efficiency and Rapid ROI</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The economic case for automated charging is compelling. In a standard 50-bay depot, Rocsys estimates that the M1 can increase operational efficiency by 75% and deliver up to $1.7 million in annual savings by reducing the need for manual oversight and maximizing vehicle uptime.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">One of the system&#8217;s most significant advantages is its interoperability. </span>The M1 works with any EV model, charger brand, and connector type, including CCS and MCS. This lets fleet operators automate depots without expensive retrofitting or being locked into a specific charging vendor.</p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Beyond Just Charging</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The launch of the M1 is part of a broader vision for the &#8220;Autonomous Depot&#8221;. </span>Rocsys has set up its system to nail these service jobs as well, such as automated interior cleaning or checks. Another corroborating factor was the company&#8217;s announcement that it has already come to contractual arrangements with a top-tier robotaxi provider.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/rocsys-raises-13m-launches-robotaxi-charging-system/" data-wpel-link="internal">Rocsys Raises $13M, Launches Robotaxi Charging System</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
			</item>
