					<description><![CDATA[<p>Squads, the main infrastructure layer for multisignature (multisig) security on Solana, revealed today that they have closed an $18 million strategic funding round. The round was raised to double down</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/squads-raises-18m-to-expand-stablecoin-platform/" data-wpel-link="internal">Squads Raises $18M to Expand Stablecoin Platform</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://squads.xyz/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Squads</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">, the main infrastructure layer for multisignature (multisig) security on Solana, revealed today that they have closed an $18 million strategic </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/hightouch-raises-150m-to-expand-data-activation-tools/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">funding </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">round.</span></p>
<p>The round was raised to double down on Altitude, the firm&#8217;s flagship operating system, to transition finance onto stablecoin rails. It was led by Solana Ventures, Coinbase Ventures, Haun Ventures, L1D, Electric Capital and Robot Ventures participating. This brings Squads&#8217; total capital raised to $42.9m, a massive vote of confidence from prominent institutional backers.</p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">The Shift from Banks to Blockchains</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Businesses all over the world have been shackled to the fractional reserve banking infrastructure. Typical business banking processes – think international payroll and treasury management – can be costly and time-consuming in terms of establishing banking relationships; be widely varied in terms of compliance procedures; and be constrained by bank operating hours.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_200457" style="width: 410px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-200457" class="size-full wp-image-200457" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Squads.jpg" alt="Squads" width="400" height="400" /><p id="caption-attachment-200457" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Squads</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">From the game-theoretic point of view, this attack model is doomed. Squads bet on that. Thanks to a programmable blockchain and stablecoins, it treats money as software. Its Altitude platform enables enterprises to manage their treasuries in a self-custodial way, making sure that their settlement accounts are mostly in stablecoins and not in a bank account. When a payment has to occur, they settle immediately on-chain, 24/7, at a tenth of the cost of old-school wire transfer.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">For the previous decade, building financial products for companies meant building on top of banks. It’s only as a result of stablecoins that we can now separate treasuries and payments from the banking system,&#8221; says Stepan Simkin, co-founder and CEO of Squads. Altitude is the operating system for this new era.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/hightouch-raises-150m-to-expand-data-activation-tools/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Hightouch Raises $150M to Expand Data Activation Tools</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Proven Traction and Market Momentum</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The raise follows explosive growth in the Altitude platform. Since going live in December 2025, Altitude has already facilitated over $200m in transactions. </span>The platform&#8217;s client mix is broad, including global exporters, design and advertising agencies, crypto, lean startups, and remote teams. The platform rests on Squads Protocol security, with $10B at stake on Solana, strengthened by Altitude’s compliance engine.</p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Strategic Timing in a Consolidating Market</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This also forms part of a trend of &#8220;traditional&#8221; fintech giants entering the stablecoin market. </span>Observers highlight Stripe&#8217;s purchase of Bridge and Mastercard&#8217;s purchase of BVNK as a reason stablecoin PSPs are seen as vital infrastructure. Finally, Squads connects with licensed PSPs such as Bridge, MoonPay, or Infinite to do bridging when transactions touch old banks.</p>
<p>This hybrid solution enables businesses to have blockchengineeringt reach into the legacy economy at the same time. Thanks to the new capital, Squads intends to scale the engineeringg team, speed up product development and extend payment network worldwide.</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/squads-raises-18m-to-expand-stablecoin-platform/" data-wpel-link="internal">Squads Raises $18M to Expand Stablecoin Platform</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
			</item>
