		<title>Parallel Web Systems Raises $100M at $2B Valuation</title>
		<link>https://ventureburn.com/parallel-web-systems-raises-100m-at-2b-valuation/</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Ekemini]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Wed, 29 Apr 2026 17:17:48 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Venture Capital]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://ventureburn.com/?p=200444</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Parallel Web System has raised $100 million of Series B funding that has valued the company at $2 billion just two years after Agrawal left the social media giant, X.</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/parallel-web-systems-raises-100m-at-2b-valuation/" data-wpel-link="internal">Parallel Web Systems Raises $100M at $2B Valuation</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://parallel.ai/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Parallel Web System</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> has raised $100 million of Series B </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/counterpart-raises-50m-for-ai-insurance-coverage/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">funding </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">that has valued the company at $2 billion just two years after Agrawal left the social media giant, X.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The Series B was led by Sequoia Capital, with other investors being Kleiner Perkins, Index Ventures and Khosla Ventures. The round brings the startup to a total of around $230m, from a $100m round in late 2024.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Redesigning the Web for Machines</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Parallel Web Systems isn&#8217;t another chatbot or consumer-focused search engine. Rather, they are constructing what Agrawal calls a &#8220;parallel&#8221; web, that is, a separate infrastructure created exclusively for autonomous AI agents.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The web of today is “built for humans” with visual pages, ads, and ranking signals that are optimised for human use. Parallel&#8217;s platform leverages a proprietary web index and custom APIs optimised for machines. This enables AI agents to conduct deep research at a pace and accuracy that Google can&#8217;t.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_200445" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-200445" class="size-large wp-image-200445" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/A-laptop-1024x531.jpg" alt="A laptop" width="1024" height="531" /><p id="caption-attachment-200445" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Unsplash</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;We believe that in the very near future, AI agents will use the web a lot more than humans do,&#8221; Agrawal said in a statement. &#8220;To do that effectively, they need a different kind of plumbing – one that prioritises data density and verifiable truth over click-through rates.&#8221;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/counterpart-raises-50m-for-ai-insurance-coverage/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Counterpart Raises $50M for AI Insurance Coverage</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">The Rise of Long-Horizon Agents</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The massive valuation reflects an industry-wide pivot toward long-horizon AI agents. Unlike current LLMs that provide quick answers to prompts, long-horizon agents are designed to work in the background for hours or days, maintaining context while completing multi-step professional workflows.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Early adopters of Parallel’s technology include prominent legal-AI firm Harvey. According to Harvey’s leadership, Parallel provides the granular control necessary to ensure their AI lawyers don&#8217;t just search the web but interrogate it, ensuring every citation and data point is cross-referenced and hallucination-free.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Sequoia partner Andrew Reed, who sits on Parallel’s board, noted that the startup is solving the &#8220;last mile&#8221; problem of AI. &#8220;Everyone is building brains,&#8221; Reed said. &#8220;Parallel is building the nervous system that lets those brains actually touch and interact with the world’s information.&#8221;</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Use of Funds and Future Outlook</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">With serving 100,000 developers on its infrastructure, Parallel will be using the $100 million to rapidly expand its scale. Part of this growth includes creating a global sales and marketing team to approach enterprise customers in high-stakes industries, such as finance, insurance and government outsourcing.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">It also plans to double its research and development team, with a focus on verifiability and provenance. In an era of rampant AI misinformation, Parallel is betting that truth-as-a-service will be the most valuable commodity in the tech stack.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">While rivals like Tavily and Exa Labs are also racing to build machine-first indexes, Parallel’s massive war chest and Agrawal’s experience scaling X’s infrastructure give the company a formidable lead in the race to define how the agentic web will function.</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/parallel-web-systems-raises-100m-at-2b-valuation/" data-wpel-link="internal">Parallel Web Systems Raises $100M at $2B Valuation</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
