		<title>Hightouch Raises $150M to Expand Data Activation Tools</title>
		<link>https://ventureburn.com/hightouch-raises-150m-to-expand-data-activation-tools/</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Ekemini]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Wed, 29 Apr 2026 16:43:44 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Venture Capital]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://ventureburn.com/?p=200436</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Hightouch has concluded a massive $150 million Series D funding round, bringing the company to a valuation of over $2.75 billion. This is really a big step change for the</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/hightouch-raises-150m-to-expand-data-activation-tools/" data-wpel-link="internal">Hightouch Raises $150M to Expand Data Activation Tools</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://hightouch.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Hightouch </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">has concluded a massive $150 million Series D </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/all3-secures-25m-for-ai-powered-construction-robots/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">funding </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">round, bringing the company to a valuation of over $2.75 billion. This is really a big step change for the Silicon Valley firm, transitioning from its core product of data synchronisation to a much more rounded AI-designed agentic marketing platform.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The round was led by Growth Equity at Goldman Sachs Alternatives and Bain Capital Ventures. The round attracted a lot of strategic partners, such as Iconiq Capital, Sapphire Ventures, Amplify Partners, Y-Combinator, and TD7, The Trade Desk&#8217;s venture capital.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">From Data Pipes to AI Agents</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Hightouch, which was started in 2019, wanted to overhaul the world of the CDP by allowing businesses to ship data from a data warehouse (say Snowflake or BigQuery) into marketing tools without any code. Today, with another fundraiser, Hightouch is staking everything on AI agents. </span></p>
<div id="attachment_200441" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-200441" class="size-large wp-image-200441" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/computer-on-a-table-1024x729.jpg" alt="computer on a table" width="1024" height="729" /><p id="caption-attachment-200441" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Unsplash</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;Marketing is sorely in need of reinvention,&#8221; said Kashish Gupta, co-founder and co-CEO of Hightouch. &#8220;We built Hightouch to rethink marketing end-to-end. Our AI agents operate directly on trusted enterprise data to find opportunities 24/7 and execute high-quality campaigns across every channel.&#8221;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This agentic approach gives marketing teams the freedom to stop configuring email flows and defining audiences. Instead, they set punchy objectives and constraints for the AI, and it figures out who to target and what creative assets to produce in order to do so.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/all3-secures-25m-for-ai-powered-construction-robots/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">All3 Secures $25M for AI-Powered Construction Robots</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Explosive Growth in a Tight Market</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Hightouch&#8217;s Series D valuation of $2.75 billion is over two times the company&#8217;s valuation of $1.2 billion just a year ago. The company has attained such a valuation through fundamentals; Hightouch revealed that it has doubled its revenue two years in a row.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Hightouch has also diversified its customer base with enterprise heavyweights including Domino&#8217;s, PetSmart, DraftKings, Ramp, and Whoop. These companies use Hightouch to actually connect their data warehouse to the products that customers see.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Strategic Roadmap</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The $150 million infusion will be used to accelerate three core areas:</span></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>AI Orchestration:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> Enabling the &#8220;brain&#8221; of the platform so that the AI agents can make more complex decisions on cross-channel campaigns.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Product Integration:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> Strengthening more with advertising platforms such as The Trade Desk for better performance marketing and attribution.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Global Scaling:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> Expanding its sales and engineering teams to support a growing international customer base.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;HighTouch has built a platform that enables companies to deploy AI agents directly on top of their most trusted data systems,&#8221; said Darren Cohen, Partner at Goldman Sachs. &#8220;We believe this approach positions them to define the next category of marketing infrastructure.&#8221;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">As the modern data stack matures, Hightouch’s success suggests that the future of the industry lies not just in moving data but in making that data act autonomously to drive business outcomes.</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/hightouch-raises-150m-to-expand-data-activation-tools/" data-wpel-link="internal">Hightouch Raises $150M to Expand Data Activation Tools</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
